    "Recall (2.9), the general principle involves here addresses the following fixed-point problem: For any given velocity field V in (x, t), the flow dictated by the ODE (2.5) will transport the initial density µ to obtain p t, and this transported p t furthermore induces the new velocity field V out defined via (2.6).",
    "It is evident that the true velocity field V is the fixed point of this map V in → V out.",
    "Thus, if we are provided with a set of vector fields {f θ } θ∈Θ, and obtain its corresponding probability flows p θ via (2.5), the ideal choice of these vector fields that approximate the true vector field is the one that minimizes the following loss function with some samples from p θ t:T t0 Ω |f θ (x, t) -V[p θ t](x, t)| 2 p θ t (x) dx dt.Moving forward, we will first establish a theoretical foundation for our method in Section 3.1 using the above loss function.",
    "Following this, we will develop a specific algorithm in Section 3.2 and conduct a detailed error analysis in Section 3.3.",
    "The Kullback-Leibler divergence error."
